				<div class="comment-text">
										<p>It sounds like there&#8217;s a fundamental misunderstanding in why English football fans object to football being called soccer. It isn&#8217;t because the term isn&#8217;t used in England, it&#8217;s because it&#8217;s an upper class term. That&#8217;s why the average fan doesn&#8217;t like it.</p>
<p>By the way it isn&#8217;t really true to say rugby didn&#8217;t take off well with the lower classes. At an early stage rugby split into two games, Rugby Union and Rugby League. The point of disagreement was wether players with jobs could be compensated for taking unpaid time off work to play. Rugby Union was strictly amateur (until very recently) and upper class, Rugby League had professionals and, particularly in some parts of Northern England, is a major working class game.</p>
				</div>
			
			</div>
			
		</div>

</li>
